<section xml:id="files_exceptions_objectives">
  <title>Objectives</title>
  <p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>To understand the concept of an <c>Exception</c> in Java.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>To be able to catch and throw exceptions.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>To be able to open files and get their meta-information.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>To be able to read and write text files.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <note>
    <p>This chapter is based on material from <em>Exercises for Think Java /
        How to Think Like a Computer Scientist</em>, a companion text for the Computer Science 075 course at
      Evergreen Valley College.</p>
  </note>
</section>
